    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(C) In nomine omnipotentis Dei aeterni. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/21">Berengarius</persName> divina favente clementia <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Si eclesiis Dei venerabilibusque locis
                        augmentum nostre munificentiae impertiri satagimus, profecto ad aeternae
                        beatitudinis gaudia nobis proficere non ambigimus. Quapropter omnium
                        fidelium sancte Dei Aeclesie nostrorumque presentium scilicet ac futurorum
                        noverit universitas, <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Count #Consiliarius_regis" ref="#people/166"
                            >Anselmum </persName><rs key="#Count #Consiliarius_regis">insignem et
                            gloriosum comitem dilectissimumque nostrum consiliarium</rs> humiliter
                        nostram exorasse <rs key="#Intercessory">clementiam</rs>, quatenus pro Dei
                        omnipotentis amore animeque nostrae remedio <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >monasterii</rs> beatissimi egregiique pontificis atque confessoris
                        Christi <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/90"
                            >Zenonis</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terrolam</rs> quandam adiacentem <placeName
                            key="#Cities #Castle" ref="#places/620"><rs key="#Cities">infra
                                civitatem Gardensem</rs>
                        </placeName><rs key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Castle"
                            >subtus castro </rs>in tribus locis positari, pertinentem <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                            ref="#estates/302"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                                ref="#places/364"><rs
                                    key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention">de
                                    corte quae dicitur Tulles </rs></placeName></geogName>nec non
                            <geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/124"><rs key="#Comitatus">de
                                Veronensi comitatu</rs></geogName>, concedere per nostri precepti
                        paginam dignaremur. Cuius ratam estimantes peticionem, iussimus hoc nostrum
                        fieri preceptum, per quod iam dictam <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >terram</rs>, in primo videlicet loco prope <rs>ripam </rs><rs
                            key="#Lakes">laci Benaci</rs> per longum perticas .V. [ad]ditis pedibus
                        sex, quae protenditur in latus pedes .XII., ex uno quidem latere <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Roads">via
                            publica</rs>, ex alio <rs>ripam </rs>iam dicti laci, ex transversus
                            <rs>iura</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Churches"><rs key="#Churches">aeclesiae Sanctae Mariae
                            </rs></orgName>ac <persName key="#Priests"><name ref="Wido"
                                >Guidonis</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiteri</rs>; in secundo igitur loco ibidem <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >terrolam</rs> quae habet per longum penicas .V. additis pedibus sex,
                        est quidem in latitudine perticas in adherentes ex uno latere <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Roads">via
                            publica</rs>, ex alio <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                            >terra item publica</rs>, ex transversus <rs>iura</rs><orgName
                            key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/90">
                            <rs key="#Monasteries">Sancti Zenonis </rs></orgName>ac <persName><name
                                ref="Sigualdus">Sigoaldi</name></persName>; item in tercio loco
                        ibidem, <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >terrolam </rs>habentem per longum perticas sex, in latitudine perticam
                        .I. additis pedibus .X., ex uno latere <rs key="#Roads">via</rs>, ex alio
                            <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                            >terra publica</rs> assistente, ex transversus <persName
                            key="#Subdeacons"><name ref="Autecherius">Autkerii </name></persName><rs
                            key="#Subdeacons">subdiaconi</rs> atque <rs>iura regis</rs>, super totum
                        numero tabulas .XXX. addimus etiam eidem eclesiae totum superiorem <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >montem</rs> Gardae, qui preminet predicte<placeName
                            key="#Cities #Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/620">
                            <rs key="#Cities">civitati </rs>Gardensi,</placeName> cum <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >aliis montibus </rs>sibi adiacentibus nostro iuri pertinentibus et <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >terras ad radicem montis</rs> ab oriente, que posite sunt <rs
                            key="#Roads">iuxta viam</rs>, pertinentes de iam dicta <rs
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention">corte</rs>,
                        in integrum cum omnibus ad se pertinentibus concedimus, et de nostro iure
                        dominioque in eius ius dominiumque transfundimus et iure proprietario
                        largimur ad habendum, tenendum, possidendum, ordinandum, vel quicquid
                        voluerit faciendum nostra regia auctoritate, absque alicuius hominis
                        contradictione vel minoratione. Si quis igitur, quod non credimus, nefario
                        ausu contra hoc nostre donationis preceptum insurgere temptaverit, sciat se
                        compositurum <rs key="#Penalty">auri optimi libras .LX</rs>., medietatem <rs
                            key="#Camera_regis">camere palatii nostri</rs> et medietatem iam dicto
                            <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs> eiusque rectoribus. Quod ut
                        verius credatur diligentiusque observetur, manu propria subter roboratum
                        anulo nostro iussimus insigniri. Signum domni (M) Berengarii serenissimi
                            regis.<persName key="#Chancellor" ref="#people/619">Ambrosius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> ad vicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/216">Ardingi </persName><rs
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops">episcopi et archicancellarii</rs>
                        recognovi et subscripsi. (SR) (SI) Data pridie non. aprilis, anno dominice
                        incarnationis .DCCCCIIII., regni vero domni Berengarii piissimi regis
                        .XVII.; indictione .VII. <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/59">Actum <rs
                                key="#Cities">Veronae</rs>.</placeName> in Dei nomine feliciter,
                        amen. </ab>
                </div>
